# Gang Wars — Locked UI Layout Standards

These three layouts are **unchangeable standards**. Match `docs/ui-standards/*.png` exactly. Do not refactor, restyle, or "improve" them.

## 1. Event popups (`.ev-popup`)

Reference: `docs/ui-standards/popup.png`

- **50/50 split**: `.ev-left` at 50%, `.ev-right` for text + CTA
- **Full-bleed art**: event image fills the entire left panel edge-to-edge — no letterboxing, inset offsets, inner borders, or clipping gaps
- Use `object-fit: cover; object-position: top center; inset: 0` on `.ev-left img`
- Gold vertical divider between panels (`border-left: 1px solid var(--amber)`)
- All narrative/event popups use `showEvent` / `showEventAsk` / feds `draw()` — never plain `.card` for events
- Standard event art: 10 PNGs in `events/` from `assets/event-grid-source.png` via `scripts/split-event-grid.py` — do not hand-edit; re-slice from source if needed
- Form modals (trade qty, bank) stay on `.card` — they are exempt

## 2. Travel screen (`.travel-play`)

Reference: `docs/ui-standards/travel.png`

- **Header**: full car image (`assets/travel-car.png`) with no border/background box; title "ON THE MOVE" plain (no bordered pill)
- **District list**: six equal-height rows, **zero gap** — stacked with horizontal dividers only, no rounded card gaps or dead space
- **Footer**: compact "GO BACK" bar
- Outer frame: `3px double var(--amber)` on `.travel-screen`
- Single-screen, no scroll

## 3. End screens (`.eos`)

Reference: `docs/ui-standards/end-screen.png`

- **Left panel (~36%)**: rank card image in double-border frame (`cards/{rank}.png`)
- **Right panel**: double-border frame with — FINAL SCORE —, amount, — ALL TIME HIGH SCORES —, dotted leaderboard rows, optional ← YOU row, PLAY AGAIN / MAIN MENU
- Every game-over path must use `renderGameOver()` / `.eos` — no alternate end layouts
- Single-screen, no scroll

## When editing

If a task would change popup, travel, or end-screen structure, spacing, image fit, or borders — **stop and ask the user first**.
